            letter = scan.nextLine();
            if (!letter.matches(&quot;[ab]&quot;)) break;
            System.out.println(&quot;You entered: &quot; + letter);
        }
    }

Method [`matches()`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#matches(java.lang.String)) that expects a regular expression as argument is used in the code above to simplify the termination condition.

*For more information on regular expressions, take a look at this* [*tutorial*](https://www.vogella.com/tutorials/JavaRegularExpressions/article.html)

